attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a Linux IRC-based DDoS bot, identified as a variant of the Kaiten (also known as Tsunami or Ziggy StarTux) malware family. It establishes a Command and Control (C2) connection to a hardcoded IRC channel (#serversovh) to receive instructions. Its primary malicious capabilities include performing various DDoS attacks (SYN flooding via 'PAN', UDP flooding), executing remote shell commands (SH, BASH, RSHELL), and self-updating. It features automated deployment of additional tools, such as the Dropbear SSH server and AES backdoors, and uses common techniques for persistence and evasion, such as process renaming and downloading payloads to /tmp and /var/bin. Relevant IOCs include the IRC channel #serversovh, the 'HackZilla' and 'Mozilla/4.75' User-Agents, and file paths like /tmp/.o and /var/bin/.
